<P><H1 align=center>DC225 – NEW PROPERTY DETAILS</H1>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Self build: </H3>Select if the property to be mortgaged 
is being built by the applicants themselves.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Currently occupied: </H3>Select if the property to be 
mortgage currently occupied by the current owners.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Applicant to occupy: </H3>Select if the applicant is the 
person who will occupy the property after the mortgage has completed.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Let or part let: </H3>Select if the property to be 
mortgaged is currently let or partly let to a third party.
<P></P>
<P><H3>First occupier: </H3>Select if the applicant is the 
first occupier of the property, ie; it is a new property.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Ex-Local authority: </H3>Select if the property to be 
mortgaged has previously been owned by the Local Authority.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Has the structure or use changed since any previous advance: </H3>Select if, since the last time the property was mortgaged, has the 
structure or use changed in any way that may affect the saleability of the 
property. If yes, include details in the box provided.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Grant applied for: </H3>Select if the customer applied 
to the council for a grant to work on the property, and input the amount in the 
Grant amount field.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Resale restrictions: </H3>There may be restrictions on 
when, or who the property can be sold to, this will be shown in the title deeds 
and detected by the acting solicitors. Any such restrictions must be detailed in 
the box provided.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Extras included in price: </H3>Are there any additional 
items that the previous owner will be leaving in the property, such as domestic 
appliances, furniture etc….or outside items such as sheds and greenhouses.
<P></P>
<P>List any such items in the box provided if these are included in the purchase 
price.</P>
